models.description:
MNI date format in compressed ISO-8601. (`YYYYMMDDThhmmss`)
- `YYYY` 4-digit year
- `MM` 2-digit month (with leading zeros < 10)
- `DD` 2-digit day (with leading zeros if < 10)
- literal `T` time start indicator
- `hh` 2-digit hours (with leading zero if < 10)
- `mm` 2-diigt minutes (with leading zero if < 10)
- `ss` 2-digit seconds (with leading zero if < 10)
- example:
  - `20241118T150800` 18-NOV-2024 15:08:00

acks.description:
When the Kafka producer (i.e. MNI) waits for acknowledgement to prevent data loss.
- `all` producer gets acknowledgement when all in-sync replicas have received record
- `leader` producer gets acknowledgement after leader received record
- `none` producer never gets acknowledgement

raw_parameter.description: internal duct identifier
internal trench identifier
intended contents of the duct, *note*: `cable` means telecommunications cables including `coax`,`copper` for twisted-pair copper cable,`ethernet`,`fiber` etc.
size classification of the duct
1/2/3/5/6/7/8/10/12/14/19/24-way (etc.) type of duct bundle
state of duct
internal duct identifier

measured vertical position from top of trench, for the United Kingdom (GB) this is typically:
  - `power`:
      - Low Voltage 450mm
      - High Voltage 450mm to 1200mm
  - `coax` 250mm to 350mm
  - `gas` 600mm
  - `water` 750mm
  - `ethernet/fiber optic` etc. 350mm

measured horizontal position from edge of trench, for the United Kingdom (GB) this is typically:
  - `power` 450mm
  - `coax` 745mm
  - `gas` 1040mm
  - `water` 1310mm
  - `ethernet/fiber optic` etc. 1579mm
unit of measure of the dimension - `cm` - metric centimetres - `mm` - metric millimetres - `m` - metric metres - `inch` - imperial inches - `feet` - imperial feet
horizontal and vertical placement of the duct within the trench

MNI date format in compressed ISO-8601. (`YYYYMMDDThhmmss`)
- `YYYY` 4-digit year
- `MM` 2-digit month (with leading zeros < 10)
- `DD` 2-digit day (with leading zeros if < 10)
- literal `T` time start indicator
- `hh` 2-digit hours (with leading zero if < 10)
- `mm` 2-diigt minutes (with leading zero if < 10)
- `ss` 2-digit seconds (with leading zero if < 10)
- example:
  - `20241118T150800` 18-NOV-2024 15:08:00

generated via machine learning predictive algorithms
- `historical` - value was supplied
- `predicted` - value was generated

- example:
  - `20241118T150800` 18-NOV-2024 15:08:00
internal trench identifier
intended contents of the duct, *note*: `cable` means telecommunications cables including `coax`,`copper` for twisted-pair copper cable,`ethernet`,`fiber` etc.
size classification of the duct
1/2/3/5/6/7/8/10/12/14/19/24-way (etc.) type of duct bundle
state of duct
internal duct identifier

measured vertical position from top of trench, for the United Kingdom (GB) this is typically:
  - `power`:
      - Low Voltage 450mm
      - High Voltage 450mm to 1200mm
  - `coax` 250mm to 350mm
  - `gas` 600mm
  - `water` 750mm
  - `ethernet/fiber optic` etc. 350mm

measured horizontal position from edge of trench, for the United Kingdom (GB) this is typically:
  - `power` 450mm
  - `coax` 745mm
  - `gas` 1040mm
  - `water` 1310mm
  - `ethernet/fiber optic` etc. 1579mm
unit of measure of the dimension - `cm` - metric centimetres - `mm` - metric millimetres - `m` - metric metres - `inch` - imperial inches - `feet` - imperial feet
horizontal and vertical placement of the duct within the trench

raw_parameter.description: internal site identifier

MNI date format in compressed ISO-8601. (`YYYYMMDDThhmmss`)
- `YYYY` 4-digit year
- `MM` 2-digit month (with leading zeros < 10)
- `DD` 2-digit day (with leading zeros if < 10)
- literal `T` time start indicator
- `hh` 2-digit hours (with leading zero if < 10)
- `mm` 2-diigt minutes (with leading zero if < 10)
- `ss` 2-digit seconds (with leading zero if < 10)
- example:
  - `20241118T150800` 18-NOV-2024 15:08:00

MNI date format in compressed ISO-8601. (`YYYYMMDD`)

raw_parameter.description: internal stream broker identifier of the Kafka broker
name of Kafka broker for human purposes
username
password, application specific passphrase or other passphrase used to authenticate with the receiving service

port number of Kafka broker
- `9092` standard port
- `9093` standard TLS encrypted port
- `9094` TLS encrypted port on AWS Managed Streaming for Apache Kafka

When the Kafka producer (i.e. MNI) waits for acknowledgement to prevent data loss.
- `all` producer gets acknowledgement when all in-sync replicas have received record
- `leader` producer gets acknowledgement after leader received record
- `none` producer never gets acknowledgement
time to wait in milliseconds before sending current batch
max size of each batch of records in megabytes (MB)
size of memory in megabytes (MB) to use per buffer
*note*: `lz4` and `snappy` compression codecs are not supported
authentication method to use
outbound host, credentials and protocol used to send stream

name.description: name of Kafka broker for human purposes

acks.description:
When the Kafka producer (i.e. MNI) waits for acknowledgement to prevent data loss.
- `all` producer gets acknowledgement when all in-sync replicas have received record
- `leader` producer gets acknowledgement after leader received record
- `none` producer never gets acknowledgement

port.description:
port number of Kafka broker
- `9092` standard port
- `9093` standard TLS encrypted port
- `9094` TLS encrypted port on AWS Managed Streaming for Apache Kafka

linger.description: time to wait in milliseconds before sending current batch

password.description: password, application specific passphrase or other passphrase used to authenticate with the receiving service

batchSize.description: max size of each batch of records in megabytes (MB)

bufferMemory.description: size of memory in megabytes (MB) to use per buffer

compressionMethod.description: *note*: `lz4` and `snappy` compression codecs are not supported

producer.description: outbound host, credentials and protocol used to send stream

kafkaProducerId.description: internal stream broker identifier of the Kafka broker
